Helen M. BARRINGER, Appellant, v. PRUDENTIAL INSURANCE COMPANY OF AMERICA. No. 8978. Circuit Court of Appeals, Third Circuit. Argued Jan. 22, 1946. Decided Feb. 1, 1946. Abraham L. Freedman, of Philadelphia, Pa. (Wolf, Block, Schorr & Solis-Cohen, of Philadelphia, Pa., on the brief), for appellant. Joseph W. Henderson, of Philadelphia, Pa. (Kendall H. Shoyer, of Philadelphia, Pa., on the brief), for appellee.

Before BIGGS, MARIS, and GOODRICH, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment of the court below is affirmed upon the opinion of Judge Kirkpatrick, 62 F.Supp. 286.
